SUMMARY: Bayern Munich's Canadian international defender Alphonso Davies suffered a "cranial bruise" after being caught in the face by the boot of Borussia Dortmund's Jude Bellingham during Saturday's draw, according to the Bundesliga champion.

TITLE: Medicare considers expanding dental benefits for certain medical conditions
SUMMARY: Proposed changes in Medicare rules could soon pave the way for a significant expansion in Medicare-covered dental services, while falling short of the comprehensive benefits that many Democratic lawmakers have advocated.

TITLE: UK brings budget forward in another attempt to reassure markets
SUMMARY: UK Finance Minister Kwasi Kwarteng will publish details of his plans to tackle ballooning government debt and kickstart economic growth on October 31, more than three weeks earlier than scheduled, in an attempt to reassure investors and restore the government's badly damaged credibility.

TITLE: Nobel Prize in economics awarded to trio including Ben Bernanke for work on financial crises
SUMMARY: Former Federal Reserve Chair Ben Bernanke, Douglas Diamond and Philip Dybvig were awarded the Nobel Prize in economics on Monday for their work on banks and financial crises.

TITLE: Jordan Poole shines in first appearance since altercation with Golden State Warriors teammate Draymond Green
SUMMARY: Jordan Poole shone in his first appearance after video emerged of an incident with his Golden State Warriors teammate Draymond Green.

TITLE: Opinion: A generation of the world's best leaders has died. Now we must look forward.
SUMMARY: We do not expect citizens to reject partisanship in the upcoming midterm elections -- indeed the authors of this commentary differ politically with each other, write Jeremi Suri and William Inboden, who argue that four leadership traits shown by 20th century leaders across the political spectrum can guide voters in assessing who has the qualities to lead in a time of such turbulence and division.

TITLE: Why the brother of Parkland school shooting victim Carmen Schentrup is against the death penalty for her killer
SUMMARY: With the conclusion of his death penalty trial looming, families of the Parkland school shooter's victims will soon learn whether he will spend the rest of his life in prison or be sentenced to death, an outcome many have indicated they prefer.

TITLE: Shooting outside NY GOP gubernatorial candidate Rep. Zeldin's home injures 2; family unhurt
SUMMARY: A shooting on the Shirley, New York, property of Rep. Lee Zeldin on Sunday left two injured, the congressman and Republican gubernatorial candidate said in a statement. Zeldin's family was unhurt.

TITLE: McCarthy told 2 officers in private meeting that Trump had no idea his supporters were attacking Capitol on January 6, newly obtained audio shows
SUMMARY: During a private meeting last summer, House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy told two police officers who defended the US Capitol on January 6, 2021, and the mother of a third who later died from his injuries that former President Donald Trump should not be blamed for the violence or waiting hours to call off his supporters who were carrying out the attack, according to newly obtained audio of the conversation.

TITLE: Texas District Attorney names San Antonio officer who shot 17-year-old in a McDonald's parking lot
SUMMARY: The Texas police officer who shot a 17-year-old man while he was eating a meal in a McDonald's parking lot last week has been named, as the teen remains in critical condition, Bexar County District Attorney Joe Gonzales said in a statement.

TITLE: A tale of two jobs markets
SUMMARY: September's hotly anticipated jobs data ended up cooling markets on Friday. Stocks fell sharply as investors evaluated the report, which showed more jobs than expected were added to the US economy and indicated that more pain-inflicting interest rate hikes from the Federal Reserve lie ahead.

TITLE: NFL: Football player Sebastian Gutierrez swaps pizza shop for the New England Patriots
SUMMARY: A former pizza shop worker is now earning his dough in the NFL after being signed by the New England Patriots.

TITLE: Erlend Fagerli: Freestyle football great makes history at 2022 Red Bull Street Style world final
SUMMARY: Erlend Fagerli is one of the most renowned freestyle footballers in the world.

TITLE: A blast hit a key bridge linking Crimea to Russia. Here's what we know
SUMMARY: A huge blast Saturday damaged the only bridge connecting annexed Crimea to the Russian mainland, causing parts of it to collapse.

TITLE: Opinion: Tuberville's racially charged remarks should be condemned
SUMMARY: Tommy Tuberville's history of racially insensitive comments likely explains why the senator from Alabama was invited to Nevada to help Republican candidates locked in tight races for US senator and governor, writes Dean Obeidallah.

TITLE: South Korean phenom Tom Kim matches Tiger Woods historical feat after second PGA Tour win
SUMMARY: Records tumbled in Tiger Woods' wake when the prodigious amateur turned professional in 1996 in one of the most breakneck accelerations to the summit that golf has ever seen.
